The paper deals with the problem of discrepancy minimization, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and mathematics. The paper proposes new algorithms for solving this problem, which involve random walks and semidefinite programming. These techniques are commonly used in areas such as data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and game theory (cs.GT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
